annotation.TEXT: Oh, hey! It's a keyhole and a key on the same screen! What a concept! Yep, so going into doors 7, 1, and 2 in that order led somewhere new! Of course, I've gotta check every pipe...
...No? A ? block with a shell? Hmm... Maybe these doors all go somewhere different now?
Ohoho! A P-switch door! So, you tricked me before! The correct door there was indeed the seventh one, but it was hidden as the P-switch door, and I actually went into door #8 last time!
Well, anyway, let's see what's new in the Spooky house...
Yep, totally. May as well grab the 28 coins that are in this part while I'm here.
Ooh, now this platform is patiently waiting for me here instead of initially moving on its own.

Oh, man. Now this cannon's firing invisible bullets! Wait, how come I didn't encounter this issue the first time around? And I had the key with me then. Did the key's presence somehow keep everything visible? That's weird.
That surprise koopa is still there, and I'm going to assume all of these turn blocks are still empty.
Huh. I wonder why that level dot appeared up there, and if there's a way to reach it...
Oh, but if I spin jump off a Boo... Aha! Now I can take the springboard further!
Ooh, this is new. Additional bullet cannons and a rotating platform. That definitely makes this part more interesting.
D'oh.
Umm... Greenman, there just maybe perhaps might possibly kind of be a sprite memory issue here, if the rotating platform's presence is causing the piranha plant to turn invisible...
Huh. So, only the leftmost pipe here goes to the bonus room... Was it like this in the previous version? (*Goes and checks*) Yep.
Overshot the crate. Oh, well. Doesn't look like there would be anything special down there anyway.
Yay for a mysterious castle crushing sound! And now I've just unlocked...
Let's try hitting that P-switch right away this time...
It's nice to see a bit more enemy activity around here.
Also, this goofy smiley face is unchanged, but there is an added parakoopa nearby.
Umm... Television generally made for grandpas?
D'oh.
Well, other than the keyholes/key thing, and some more upside-down munchers, this part appears to be the same. Now, what about the next area?
The ghostly koopas are still here, and hopefully I won't take a couple of stupid hits from them this time!
Whoops, I didn't mean to fall yet! I just slipped while contemplating whether to check if the fence was still down there. Fortunately, it is!
Well, may as well see if the password's the same as before. Okay, so doors 1, 1, 4, and 7...
And, going in any door other than the correct one just resets the whole thing, right?
Alright. Well, secret exit get!
NOOOOO!!! Saw used Cut! Critical hit! Mario lost his reserve power up and fainted!

Well, that was an interesting twist on the password entry. However, I don't know if such a twist was entirely necessary. I mean, the trick would only be most effective on someone that already knows or figured out that the password is 1147...
Maybe I can find a keyhole that matches this key...
Alright, I'm fully powered up again. Let's see how long that lasts...
Oh, that red koopa's position has been changed so it can't ambush me suddenly here.
Nuts. I thought maybe I could hit one of the yellow blocks with the key. Nuts to the key anyway. If I ever see a keyhole, I'll come back for it.
To be continued...
Alright, well it looks like this level has had some decent improvements. That mind-screwing key is still there though, and what was the deal with that added goal sphere in a cement box?
And, I've reached midpoint, so now to turn around and make my way back to where I was. (Hmm... Maybe it would've been faster if I had just taken the pipe again...)
Wait, what? Did that piranha plant just vanish?
Man, that would've sucked for me if it turned out he had removed this safety net!
The path to the MOON is still here, and now would be a good time for me to check those other pipes.
Four d'ohs and only one yay. Not a very good run there...
Also, if only some of those bullet cannons actually fire, you might want to switch out the non-firing cannons with different blocks, but that's up to you.
Yep, there it is. May as well confirm that this door leads to the same place.
And then, maybe later, I'll see if there's a way to reach this... crushed castle over here? What the heck? And where'd that other level dot go? Now that's really weird...
Okay, moving on... Ah, this platform was waiting for me too. How nice of it.
Now it's a multi-coin block? Wait, I just went in door #7, followed by door #1... Oh, how clever of you, Greenman! I bet if I go into door #2 right now, I'll find something cool!
The pipe's exit is the same as before. Now, hopefully I can backtrack back to midpoint like before...
There's that pop-out 1-up, just like last time. I think the Boo chain is new, though.
Ooh, there's an island south of Time to Swim where the level More swimming used to be. I wonder what'll be new there? But, that'll probably have to wait until the next episode at least.
I don't think there's anything up in the air back here, though...
Ha! This koopa can't potentially surprise attack me if I stick to the upper route!
Argh! I got a bullet in me butt!
What? A P-switch? And some enemies? This is new, but the correct door here is still number 7, right?
For right now, I want to check out Spooky house again, and see if there is a keyhole I missed. Time for fast forward!
Okay, I somehow got past that off screen part in one piece. I should have it easy now.
Ooh, there's new upside-down munchers that I can't reach.

Well, guess what fancy stunt I won't be trying again! Also, I always hate it when I take a hit while falling to certain death anyway, and just because of that hit, I'm gypped out of my reserve power up!
That paradoxial message is the same though, and it doesn't affect Mario anymore now! (It's kind of like the chicken pox-- After you've endured it once, it won't affect you ever again!)
The same is not true of the second platform however, and that could make jumping to it kind of tricky if they're way out of sync.
There's a springboard here too...
Demo count: 1
Oh, hey there Digging Chuck and caged goal sphere. How's it going? (Why was that caged goal sphere added anyway?)
Huh. I wonder why there's no parakoopa around here anymore... Did it fail to drink its Red Bull today?
Still nothing special up here...
No keyholes here now, but there's a key instead?
D'oh.
Okay, I'm going to do something foolish and possibly deadly here-- I'm going to try to spin jump on a saw in order to keep the key with me!
Oh, this is new. You're having me do bullet cannon hopping before reaching the goal, eh? Also, this removes the possibility of me doing the "climb on air" glitch as well.
Okay, I'm going to assume this upper door is the same as before, so I'll check out the lower route now, and then just take the door at the end of that route if it's also unchanged.
That was a nice trick shot on that shell. As for finding any new stuff, I think it's a bust...
Now I know I didn't completely take out the Chucks here yet...
Hello, this is SomeGuy712x, and welcome back to more possible insanity! Now, let's go see what's changed in Tight rope walking...
Moon count: 2
Hmm... Up or down? Well...
Well, whatever these letters stand for, I'll be checking this new place out next time!
Oops. I made the message box despawn due to the sprite limit. I bet if I kill a plant or something, I can make it respawn.
Hmm... Doesn't look like I can go any farther back than this with the springboard...
Yay.
Okay, now that I don't have a key that gives me idiot syndrome, I'll do this part the safer way. And, I believe I'll be completely safe if I hang out on the very bottom of the rope.
D'oh.
Hmm... Now, with this springboard, I should be able to check out a lot more of the level...
I see this teasing key is still here, just like before.
Actually, I'm going to leave the key behind. If I find a keyhole, I'll come back for it, but until then, it's probably just going to get in the way.
Nuts. Did I mess up? That was door number 7, right? I mean, it wouldn't make any sense for the password to be anything other than 1147...
